#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:2
msgid "Skip builds based on conditions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:4
msgid ""
"Read the Docs provides a special build cancellation mechanism that allows "
"you to programmatically skip builds based on custom conditions. This is "
"useful when you want to avoid unnecessary documentation builds, saving build "
"time and resources."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:8
msgid "Recommended: use Automation Rules with webhook filters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:10
msgid ""
"For most cases, the recommended way to skip builds is to use :doc:"
"`automation rules </automation-rules>` with **webhook filters**. This lets "
"you filter which changes can trigger builds, such as **only building when "
"files matching a pattern are changed** (for example, files under ``docs/`` "
"or ``.readthedocs.yaml``), or building when a commit message or pull request "
"labels match a pattern."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:17
msgid ""
"Webhook filters are available for projects connected through the :doc:"
"`GitHub App integration </reference/git-integration>`. For other Git "
"providers, or for conditions that require shell logic at build time, keep "
"using the exit code ``183`` mechanism documented below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:25
msgid "Table of contents"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:28
msgid "How it works"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:30
msgid ""
"When any command in your build process exits with the special exit code "
"``183``, Read the Docs will immediately cancel the build. The build will be "
"marked as cancelled and will not consume build time or resources beyond that "
"point."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:34
msgid "Why exit code 183?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:36
msgid ""
"The exit code 183 was chosen because it represents the word \"skip\" encoded "
"in ASCII."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:38
msgid ""
">>> sum(list(\"skip\".encode(\"ascii\")))\n"
"439\n"
">>> 439 % 256  # Unix exit codes are limited to 0-255\n"
"183"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:45
msgid ""
"The 256 modulo operation is necessary because `Unix exit codes are limited "
"to 0-255 <https://tldp.org/LDP/abs/html/exitcodes.html>`_, and any value "
"larger than 255 is automatically reduced by taking the modulo 256."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:49
msgid "When to skip builds"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:51
msgid ""
"There are several scenarios where you might want to skip documentation "
"builds:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:53
msgid "**Save resources on irrelevant changes**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:54
msgid ""
"Skip builds when changes don't affect documentation, such as changes only to "
"source code, tests, or CI configuration files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:57
msgid "**Avoid redundant builds**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:58
msgid ""
"Skip builds for draft pull requests, work-in-progress branches, or commits "
"with specific markers like ``[skip ci]`` in the commit message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:61
msgid "**Conditional documentation updates**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:62
msgid ""
"Only build documentation when specific files or directories are modified, "
"such as the ``docs/`` folder or configuration files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:65
msgid "**Branch-specific logic**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:66
msgid ""
"Skip builds on certain branches that don't require documentation updates, "
"such as experimental or development branches."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:70
msgid "Examples"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:72
msgid ""
"The following examples demonstrate common use cases for skipping builds. All "
"examples use the :ref:`config-file/v2:build.jobs` configuration key in your "
"``.readthedocs.yaml`` file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:77
msgid "Skip builds when documentation files haven't changed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:81
msgid ""
"If your project is connected through the GitHub App, using an :doc:"
"`automation rule </automation-rules>` with a *Changed files* webhook filter "
"is the recommended approach for skipping builds. Automation rules allow for "
"builds to be skipped entirely, whereas the approach below can only *cancel* "
"a running build."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:87
msgid ""
"This example skips pull request builds when there are no changes to "
"documentation-related files compared to the ``main`` branch:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:90
#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:120
#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:143
#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:165
msgid ".readthedocs.yaml"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:90
msgid ""
"version: 2\n"
"build:\n"
"  os: \"ubuntu-22.04\"\n"
"  tools:\n"
"    python: \"3.12\"\n"
"  jobs:\n"
"    post_checkout:\n"
"      # Cancel building pull requests when there aren't changes in the docs "
"directory or YAML file.\n"
"      # If there are no changes (git diff exits with 0) we force the command "
"to return with 183.\n"
"      # This is a special exit code on Read the Docs that will cancel the "
"build immediately.\n"
"      - |\n"
"        if [ \"$READTHEDOCS_VERSION_TYPE\" = \"external\" ] && git diff --"
"quiet origin/main -- docs/ .readthedocs.yaml;\n"
"        then\n"
"          exit 183;\n"
"        fi"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:109
msgid "You can customize this example by:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:111
msgid ""
"Adding more paths to check: ``docs/ .readthedocs.yaml requirements/docs.txt``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:112
msgid ""
"Checking against a different branch: ``origin/develop`` instead of ``origin/"
"main``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:113
msgid ""
"Using different comparison operators to check for specific file patterns"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:116
msgid "Skip builds based on commit message"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:118
msgid ""
"This example skips builds when the commit message contains ``[skip ci]`` or "
"``[ci skip]``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:120
msgid ""
"version: 2\n"
"build:\n"
"  os: \"ubuntu-22.04\"\n"
"  tools:\n"
"    python: \"3.12\"\n"
"  jobs:\n"
"    post_checkout:\n"
"      # Use `git log` to check if the latest commit contains \"skip ci\",\n"
"      # in that case exit the command with 183 to cancel the build\n"
"      - (git --no-pager log --pretty=\"tformat:%s -- %b\" -1 | paste -s -d "
"\" \" | grep -viq \"skip ci\") || exit 183"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:134
msgid ""
"This pattern is commonly used in CI/CD systems to skip builds for "
"administrative commits, such as version bumps or documentation typos."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:138
msgid "Skip builds for specific branch patterns"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:140
msgid ""
"This example skips builds for branches that match certain patterns, such as "
"personal development branches:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:143
msgid ""
"version: 2\n"
"build:\n"
"  os: \"ubuntu-22.04\"\n"
"  tools:\n"
"    python: \"3.12\"\n"
"  jobs:\n"
"    post_checkout:\n"
"      # Skip builds for branches starting with \"dev/\" or \"experiment/\"\n"
"      - |\n"
"        if echo \"$READTHEDOCS_GIT_IDENTIFIER\" | grep -qE \"^(dev|"
"experiment)/\"; then\n"
"          exit 183;\n"
"        fi"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:160
msgid "Skip builds based on file types"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:162
msgid ""
"This example skips builds when all changes are to non-documentation files, "
"such as only images or data files:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:165
msgid ""
"version: 2\n"
"build:\n"
"  os: \"ubuntu-22.04\"\n"
"  tools:\n"
"    python: \"3.12\"\n"
"  jobs:\n"
"    post_checkout:\n"
"      # Skip if only non-documentation files changed (e.g., only images or "
"data files)\n"
"      - |\n"
"        if [ \"$READTHEDOCS_VERSION_TYPE\" = \"external\" ]; then\n"
"          # Get list of changed files\n"
"          CHANGED_FILES=$(git diff --name-only origin/main)\n"
"          # Check if any changed files are documentation-related.\n"
"          # If ALL files are non-documentation (grep finds no documentation "
"files),\n"
"          # then we skip the build by exiting with 183.\n"
"          if ! echo \"$CHANGED_FILES\" | grep -qE \"\\.(rst|md|py|yaml|yml|"
"txt|toml)$\"; then\n"
"            exit 183;\n"
"          fi\n"
"        fi"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:189
msgid "Best practices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:191
msgid "When implementing skip build logic, consider these best practices:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:193
msgid "**Test your conditions locally**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:194
msgid ""
"Before deploying skip build logic, test your bash conditions locally to "
"ensure they work as expected. Remember that the condition failing will "
"cancel your build."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:197
msgid "**Be specific with your conditions**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:198
msgid ""
"Write clear and specific conditions to avoid accidentally skipping builds "
"that should run. Overly broad conditions might prevent important "
"documentation updates."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:201
msgid "**Document your skip logic**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:202
msgid ""
"Add comments in your ``.readthedocs.yaml`` file explaining why builds are "
"skipped and under what conditions. This helps future maintainers understand "
"the configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:205
msgid "**Consider the impact on pull requests**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:206
msgid ""
"If you skip builds on pull requests, reviewers won't have preview "
"documentation. Make sure this aligns with your team's review process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:209
msgid "**Use environment variables**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:210
msgid ""
"Leverage :doc:`Read the Docs environment variables </reference/environment-"
"variables>` like ``READTHEDOCS_VERSION_TYPE`` to make your conditions more "
"precise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:214
msgid "Limitations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:216
msgid "Be aware of these limitations when using the skip build feature:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:218
msgid "**No partial cancellation**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:219
msgid ""
"Once a build is cancelled with exit code 183, the entire build stops "
"immediately. You cannot selectively skip only certain parts of the build "
"process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:222
msgid "**Not available in configuration file**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:223
msgid ""
"You cannot skip builds using conditions in the ``.readthedocs.yaml`` "
"configuration syntax itself. All logic must be implemented in bash commands."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:226
msgid "**Build is counted as cancelled**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:227
msgid ""
"Cancelled builds appear in your build history as cancelled, not as skipped "
"or successful. This is different from builds that never start due to branch/"
"version filters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:230
msgid "**No failure notifications are sent**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:231
msgid ""
"When a build is skipped via exit code ``183``, Read the Docs does not send "
"``build:failed`` webhook notifications or failure emails for it. The build "
"is treated as an intentional skip rather than a failure. Note that a ``build:"
"triggered`` webhook may still have been delivered earlier, before the build "
"command had a chance to exit with ``183``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:237
msgid "**Pull request status is reported as successful**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:238
msgid ""
"When a commit status is sent to your Git provider (for pull request builds), "
"it is reported as successful so that the pull request is not blocked from "
"merging."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:243
msgid "Troubleshooting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:245
msgid "**Build is not being skipped**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:246
msgid "Verify your condition logic is correct by testing it locally"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:247
msgid "Check that the command is returning exit code 183 specifically"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:248
msgid ""
"Ensure you're using the correct :doc:`environment variables </reference/"
"environment-variables>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:249
msgid "Review the build logs to see if your condition is being evaluated"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:251
msgid "**Builds are being skipped unexpectedly**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:252
msgid "Review your condition logic to ensure it's not too broad"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:253
msgid "Check for syntax errors in your bash commands"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:254
msgid "Verify that file paths and branch names are correct"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:255
msgid "Test the condition in different scenarios (PRs, branches, tags)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:257
msgid "**Cannot access Git information**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:258
msgid ""
"Some Git operations require a full clone. If you need Git history, you might "
"need to `unshallow the clone <https://docs.readthedocs.io/en/stable/build-"
"customization.html#unshallow-git-clone>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/build/skip-build.rst:260
msgid ""
"Ensure you're running your skip logic in ``post_checkout`` to have access to "
"the repository"
msgstr ""
